  
                    1.1 INTRODUCTION TO KERNEL.  changes added

    Kernal is the heart of Linux O/S. It manages resource of Linux O/S. Resources means facilities available in Linux.
    For Ex.Facility to store data, print data on printer,memory,filemanagement etc.
    Kernel decides who will use this resource, for how long and when.
    it runs your programs(or set up execute binary files) it's Memory resident portion of liux.
    It performance following tasks.

 > I/O management
 > Process management
 > Device management
 > File management
 > Memory management


